Volkswagen AG &lt;VOWG.F>managing board chairman Carl Hahn said the company was equal tothe challenge of overcoming potential losses from allegedlyfraudulent currency transactions.    He said the potential losses of 480 mln marks were asetback for VW but added the company's past conservativefinancial management meant VW was up to the challenge.    VW would not cut back on investment or fringe benefitsbecause of the possible currency losses, he told workers in aspeech before driving the 50 millionth vehicle produced by VWoff the assembly line. Reuter&#3;